<section class="wml section" id="wml">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Flagship Project</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">World Model Lens</h2>

    <div class="wml__intro reveal">
      <p>
        World Model Lens is a research-oriented software toolkit for analyzing, debugging, and understanding world models — including Dreamer-style RSSMs, JEPA, transformers, video prediction models, and robotics/autonomous-driving world models.
      </p>
      <p>
        It provides observability, replay, causal analysis, safety auditing, and probing tools so researchers can inspect activations, beliefs, uncertainties, and failure modes in a structured way. The goal is to make world models more interpretable, safer, and easier to debug.
      </p>
      <p>
        World Model Lens standardizes logging, analysis, and benchmarks so that different groups can compare and reproduce findings on world-model behavior.
      </p>
      <p class="wml__inspiration">
        Inspired by Neel Nanda's TransformerLens and the AgentLens library from MATS alumni, adapted for world models rather than language models.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Pillars -->
    <h3 style="font-size: var(--fs-lg); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--s-6);" class="reveal">Feature Pillars</h3>
    <div class="wml__pillars">
      <div class="pillar reveal">
        <div class="pillar__icon pillar__icon--obs">
